    <div class="content-section">
      <h2>Methodology</h2>
      <p>This list aggregates widely held and popular securities that distribute dividends on a monthly basis, contrary to the standard quarterly payout schedule of most U.S. equities. The list includes real estate investment trusts (REITs), business development companies (BDCs), traditional equities, and exchange-traded funds (ETFs).</p>
      <p>Data metrics such as Price, Annual Dividend, Dividend Yield, and Market Capitalization are sourced directly from current market feeds. Yields are calculated based on the trailing twelve-month (TTM) distribution or forward indicated yield depending on the asset class convention. It is essential to recognize that extremely high yields (e.g., above 10%) often indicate significant market pricing of risk, potential payout cuts, or destructive return of capital mechanisms (especially in certain closed-end funds or high-yield ETFs).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What are the best monthly dividend stocks?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Some of the most popular monthly dividend stocks include Realty Income (O), Main Street Capital (MAIN), STAG Industrial (STAG), and Agree Realty (ADC). These are largely concentrated in the REIT and BDC sectors, which have structural requirements to distribute the majority of their taxable income to shareholders.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is the highest yielding monthly dividend stock?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Often, Business Development Companies (BDCs) like Prospect Capital (PSEC) or Mortgage REITs like ARMOUR Residential REIT (ARR) offer the highest monthly yields, sometimes exceeding 12-15%. However, these high yields carry significantly more risk of principal loss and dividend cuts than lower-yielding alternatives.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Which ETFs pay monthly dividends?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Popular ETFs that pay monthly dividends include JPMorgan Equity Premium Income ETF (JEPI), Invesco S&P 500 High Dividend Low Volatility ETF (SPHD), SPDR Dow Jones Industrial Average ETF (DIA), and various preferred stock or bond ETFs like PFF. Covered call ETFs are particularly well-known for monthly payouts.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Are monthly dividend stocks a good investment?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Monthly dividend stocks can be excellent for income investors seeking regular cash flow to cover living expenses or for compounding returns faster through frequent reinvestment (DRIP). However, total return and dividend safety are more important than payout frequency; never buy a poor business simply because it pays monthly.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is Realty Income (O) a good stock to buy?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Realty Income (O) is considered a blue-chip REIT and is famous for trademarking 'The Monthly Dividend Company.' It has a long track record of consistent monthly payouts and slow, steady dividend increases, making it a staple in many income-focused portfolios.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
  <script is:inline>
// Embedded Data
    const rawData = [{"ticker":"PSEC","name":"Prospect Capital Corporation","yield":20.3,"dividend":0.54,"price":2.65,"type":"BDC","marketCap":1278598016},{"ticker":"ARR","name":"ARMOUR Residential REIT, Inc.","yield":16.14,"dividend":2.88,"price":17.41,"type":"REIT","marketCap":2078491392},{"ticker":"DX","name":"Dynex Capital, Inc.","yield":14.78,"dividend":2,"price":13.33,"type":"REIT","marketCap":2692436992},{"ticker":"AGNC","name":"AGNC Investment Corp.","yield":13.5,"dividend":1.44,"price":10.39,"type":"REIT","marketCap":11520128000},{"ticker":"NLY","name":"Annaly Capital Management, Inc.","yield":12.47,"dividend":2.8,"price":22.01,"type":"REIT","marketCap":15811696640},{"ticker":"GLAD","name":"Gladstone Capital Corporation","yield":10.76,"dividend":1.94,"price":17.66,"type":"BDC","marketCap":398993568},{"ticker":"JEPQ","name":"JPMorgan Nasdaq Equity Premium Income ETF","yield":10.58,"dividend":6.02,"price":56.86,"type":"ETF","marketCap":34604126000},{"ticker":"JEPI","name":"JPMorgan Equity Premium Income ETF","yield":7.91,"dividend":4.52,"price":57.18,"type":"ETF","marketCap":44961915000},{"ticker":"SLG","name":"SL Green Realty Corp.","yield":7.49,"dividend":2.83,"price":37.88,"type":"REIT","marketCap":2875435776},{"ticker":"SBR","name":"Sabine Royalty Trust","yield":6.74,"dividend":5.04,"price":73.95,"type":"Stock","marketCap":1078142464},{"ticker":"PBA","name":"Pembina Pipeline Corporation","yield":6.38,"dividend":2.84,"price":44.48,"type":"Stock","marketCap":25853153280},{"ticker":"EPR","name":"EPR Properties","yield":6.2,"dividend":3.52,"price":55.8,"type":"REIT","marketCap":4269816320},{"ticker":"LTC","name":"LTC Properties, Inc.","yield":5.88,"dividend":2.28,"price":39.03,"type":"REIT","marketCap":1893335936},{"ticker":"PFF","name":"iShares Preferred and Income Securities ETF","yield":5.87,"dividend":1.82,"price":30.85,"type":"ETF","marketCap":12909181952},{"ticker":"MAIN","name":"Main Street Capital Corporation","yield":5.35,"dividend":3.03,"price":54.66,"type":"BDC","marketCap":4925130240},{"ticker":"O","name":"Realty Income Corporation","yield":4.97,"dividend":3.22,"price":65.03,"type":"REIT","marketCap":60853444608},{"ticker":"SPHD","name":"Invesco S&P 500 High Dividend Low Volatility ETF","yield":3.94,"dividend":1.96,"price":49.77,"type":"ETF","marketCap":3429118460},{"ticker":"STAG","name":"STAG Industrial, Inc.","yield":3.89,"dividend":1.49,"price":38.04,"type":"REIT","marketCap":7419156992},{"ticker":"ADC","name":"Agree Realty Corporation","yield":3.86,"dividend":3.08,"price":79.66,"type":"REIT","marketCap":9589146624},{"ticker":"PEY","name":"Invesco High Yield Equity Dividend Achievers ETF","yield":3.77,"dividend":0.79,"price":20.9209,"type":"ETF","marketCap":970729792},{"ticker":"DGRW","name":"WisdomTree U.S. Quality Dividend Growth Fund","yield":1.34,"dividend":1.2,"price":89.67,"type":"ETF","marketCap":16244789200},{"ticker":"DIA","name":"State Street SPDR Dow Jones Industrial Average ETF Trust","yield":1.18,"dividend":5.62,"price":467.48,"type":"ETF","marketCap":37979430912}];

    // Formatting utilities
    const formatCurrency = (val) => {
      if (val === null || val === undefined) return 'N/A';
      return new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', { style: 'currency', currency: 'USD' }).format(val);
    };

    const formatMarketCap = (val) => {
      if (val === null || val === undefined) return 'N/A';
      if (val >= 1e9) return '$' + (val / 1e9).toFixed(2) + 'B';
      if (val >= 1e6) return '$' + (val / 1e6).toFixed(2) + 'M';
      return formatCurrency(val);
    };

    // State
    let currentData = [...rawData];
    let sortCol = 'yield';
    let sortDesc = true;

    // Elements
    const tableBody = document.getElementById('tableBody');
    const searchInput = document.getElementById('searchInput');
    const filterBtns = document.querySelectorAll('.filter-btn');
    const ths = document.querySelectorAll('th[data-sort]');

    // Render Table
    const renderTable = () => {
      tableBody.innerHTML = '';
      if (currentData.length === 0) {
        tableBody.innerHTML = '<tr><td colspan="6" style="text-align:center; color: var(--text-muted); padding: 32px;">No matching securities found.</td></tr>';
        return;
      }

      currentData.forEach(item => {
        const tr = document.createElement('tr');
        tr.innerHTML = `
          <td>
            <span class="ticker">${item.ticker}</span>
            <span class="name">${item.name}</span>
          </td>
          <td><span class="type-badge type-${item.type}">${item.type}</span></td>
          <td class="num-val">${formatCurrency(item.price)}</td>
          <td class="num-val">${formatCurrency(item.dividend)}</td>
          <td class="num-val yield-val">${item.yield ? item.yield.toFixed(2) + '%' : 'N/A'}</td>
          <td class="num-val">${formatMarketCap(item.marketCap)}</td>
        `;
        tableBody.appendChild(tr);
      });
    };

    // Filter and Sort Logic
    const applyFilters = () => {
      const searchTerm = searchInput.value.toLowerCase();
      const activeFilterBtn = document.querySelector('.filter-btn.active');
      const typeFilter = activeFilterBtn.dataset.filter;

      currentData = rawData.filter(item => {
        const matchesSearch = item.ticker.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm) ||
                              item.name.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm);
        const matchesType = typeFilter === 'all' || item.type === typeFilter;
        return matchesSearch && matchesType;
      });

      // Sort
      currentData.sort((a, b) => {
        let valA = a[sortCol];
        let valB = b[sortCol];

        if (valA === null) valA = sortDesc ? -Infinity : Infinity;
        if (valB === null) valB = sortDesc ? -Infinity : Infinity;

        if (typeof valA === 'string') {
          return sortDesc ? valB.localeCompare(valA) : valA.localeCompare(valB);
        }
        return sortDesc ? valB - valA : valA - valB;
      });

      renderTable();
    };

    // Event Listeners
    searchInput.addEventListener('input', applyFilters);
    searchInput.addEventListener('keyup', applyFilters); // Important for playwright tests

    filterBtns.forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        filterBtns.forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
        btn.classList.add('active');
        applyFilters();
      });
    });

    ths.forEach(th => {
      th.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const col = th.dataset.sort;
        if (sortCol === col) {
          sortDesc = !sortDesc;
        } else {
          sortCol = col;
          sortDesc = true;
        }

        // Update header UI
        ths.forEach(t => {
          t.classList.remove('sort-asc', 'sort-desc');
        });
        th.classList.add(sortDesc ? 'sort-desc' : 'sort-asc');

        applyFilters();
      });
    });

    // Initialize charts
    const initCharts = () => {
      Chart.defaults.color = '#6a7a90';
      Chart.defaults.font.family = 'Inter, sans-serif';

      // Chart 1: Average Yield by Type
      const types = ['REIT', 'BDC', 'ETF', 'Stock'];
      const avgYieldsByType = types.map(t => {
        const items = rawData.filter(d => d.type === t && d.yield !== null);
        if(items.length === 0) return 0;
        return items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.yield, 0) / items.length;
      });

      const ctxType = document.getElementById('typeChart').getContext('2d');
      new Chart(ctxType, {
        type: 'bar',
        data: {
          labels: types,
          datasets: [{
            label: 'Avg Yield %',
            data: avgYieldsByType,
            backgroundColor: [
              'rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.7)', // REIT
              'rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.7)',  // BDC
              'rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.7)',  // ETF
              'rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.7)'   // Stock
            ],
            borderColor: [
              '#10b981', '#f59e0b', '#8b5cf6', '#3b82f6'
            ],
            borderWidth: 1,
            borderRadius: 4
          }]
        },
        options: {
          responsive: true,
          maintainAspectRatio: false,
          plugins: {
            legend: { display: false },
            tooltip: {
              callbacks: {
